

     
      Roller is a typical Java web application with a three layer architecture. A Struts and JSP based presentation layer, a business layer made up of facade style interfaces and POJOs, and persistence layer interfaces to encapsulate the persistence mechanism. Roller provides a web user interface, an XML representation (also known as newsfeeds), and a web services interface.   Link to this resource to find the architecture of Roller Weblogger.  [Resource-Type: Weblink/Case Study; Category: Java/J2EE, Level: IMD/ADV, XRating: 4.5]  
     
    
